@datakurre Plone coredev 5.0 and 5.1 both use a checked out master branch, and have version 1.8.2 in their versions.  According to the changelog, there are backwards incompatible changes on master.  Jenkins is still happy with master on both coredevs.

I am inclined to say: coredev 5.0 should use the 1.x branch, and 5.1 can use the 2.x versions from master.  Does that make sense?

@albertduran Sorry for the long silence. Now I finally see the issue in your tile schema, and it's pretty technical.

The ``ConstraintNotSatisfied`` is due to ``value_type=schema.Choice`` which implictly requires the value to be an (encoded) byte string. But the vocabulary in question ``plone.app.vocabularies.Keywords`` probably provides accented tags as unicode.

The correct solution should be to define the schema similarly to how it's done for the default tags field: https://github.com/plone/plone.app.dexterity/blob/master/plone/app/dexterity/behaviors/metadata.py#L101 (There the field is defined as tuple of text/unicode lines, but the field has keywords widget.)

