@grlee77 It could well be that numpy updated their `mean` function to use a more numerically-stable summation algorithm after 1.6. There's talk of bumping the requirement to numpy 1.7 before scikit-image 0.12, so you might be off the hook after a rebase.

Other than that I have the following style change recommendations, in decreasing order of importance:

- X, Y -> im_test, im_true / ar_test, ar_true
- foo.mean() -> np.mean(foo) (ditto for min, max, etc)
- mse -> mean_squared_error. I think PSNR is much more commonly used as an acronym, whereas MSE is often referred to by its full name, e.g. in conversation. To me, just "mse" is hard to parse, especially because of the lowercase.

